Three people who had eaten contaminated meat were admitted at Samburu County Referral Hospital on Monday.Medical superintendent Robert Nato said the old man and two women were hospitalised in critical condition.He said they were part of a group of nine family members who said they ate the meat of a goat that died after an injection.Nato said the patients vomited and complained of severe abdominal pain, and headaches. The children were not badly affected; they were treated and discharged immediately, he said.Samburu Central OCPD Abaggarro Guyo said 15 people ate the poisonous meat but that six were not affected.Also read: 24 hospitalised in Samburu after eating dead cow's meat